import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import umap
import hdbscan

data clustering with hdbscan¶

In this notebook, we will try and get a meaningful clustering of the states in the US based on the rtaes of the different crimes, and then plot the results with matplotlib after reducing the dimension of the data with umap.

In [7]:
X = crimes.iloc[:, 3:].values
labels = crimes.iloc[:, 1].values
In [10]:
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
reducer = umap.UMAP()
scaled_X=StandardScaler().fit_transform(X)
X_umap=reducer.fit_transform(scaled_X)
In [11]:
plt.rcParams["figure.figsize"] = (10,10)
plt.scatter(X_umap[:, 0], X_umap[:, 1],s=300 )
for label, x, y in zip(labels, X_umap[:, 0], X_umap[:, 1]):
    plt.annotate(label, xy=(x, y), xytext=(-0.2, 0.2), textcoords='offset points')
plt.show()

In [14]:
import seaborn as sns
plt.rcParams["figure.figsize"] = (10,10)
color_palette = sns.color_palette('Paired', 12)
cluster_colors = [color_palette[x] if x >= 0 else (0.5, 0.5, 0.5) for x in clusterer.labels_]
cluster_member_colors = [sns.desaturate(x, p) for x, p in zip(cluster_colors, clusterer.probabilities_)]
plt.scatter(X_umap[:, 0], X_umap[:, 1],s=300 ,c=cluster_colors)
for label, x, y in zip(labels, X_umap[:, 0], X_umap[:, 1]):
    plt.annotate(label, xy=(x, y), xytext=(-0.2, 0.2), textcoords='offset points')
plt.show()
